    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="330"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Harvey</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 298.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to communicate herewith a copy
                    of a note which has just reached me from the United States consulate at Madeira,
                    having reference to the suspicious steamer Laurel, to which the attention of our
                    public agents had been recently called by telegraphic despatches and
                    correspondence of Mr. Dudley at Liverpool.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES E. HARVEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
